{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"45589b3a-b1b2-4d93-ad80-f5a8942fcdc1","content":"CLR activation logs won't help here. They only capture how the .NET runtime is **loaded and selected** (e.g., wrong runtime version, shim failures, FOD dialogs) — not application-level exceptions.\n\nA **NullReferenceException** is an app-level bug (dereferencing a `null` reference), not a CLR activation issue.\n\n**Better approaches to diagnose this:**\n\n1. **Check the stack trace** — it tells you exactly which line has the null dereference.\n2. **Enable first-chance exception logging** — run with a debugger or set `DOTNET_EnableDiagnostics=1`.\n3. **Collect a crash dump** — use `dotnet-dump collect` or `DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump=1` and analyze with `dotnet-dump analyze`.\n4. **Review startup code** — look for uninitialized services, missing DI registrations, or config values that are null.\n\nDo you have a stack trace or crash dump you can share? I can help analyze either.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"85a9fd07-ff4b-4c84-b0b7-cf0cf14e2f29","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking me to analyze CLR activation logs to diagnose a NullReferenceException in their .NET app. Let me check if there's a relevant skill for this.\n\nLooking at the available skills, I see \"clr-activation-debugging\" which \"Diagnoses .NET Framework CLR activation issues using CLR activation logs (CLRLoad logs) produced by mscoree.dll.\"\n\nHowever, a NullReferenceException after startup is not a CLR activation issue. CLR activation logs are about how the CLR (Common Language Runtime) is loaded and initialized — things like which runtime version is selected, whether the shim picks the right runtime, etc. A NullReferenceException is an application-level bug, not a CLR activation problem.\n\n\nThe skill description specifically covers scenarios like the shim picking the wrong runtime or failing to load any runtime, which doesn't apply here. I should explain to the user that CLR activation logs won't help with this particular exception and suggest more appropriate debugging approaches instead.","outputTokens":561,"requestId":"6089:13C8F3:1039009:147A35D:69FFE098"},"id":"970b23d1-0a13-4c6e-9014-726be0a77c5f","timestamp":"2026-05-10T01:34:30.344Z","parentId":"d3f12ae6-cf4d-4a4b-879a-7653595d0547"}
